    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AgeFilterMenu
    AgeFilterMenu handles the UI logic for filtering applicants by their age.
    Applicant
    The Applicant class represents a user in the system who is an applicant.
    ApplicantFilterManager
    The ApplicantFilterManager class provides filtering capabilities for a list of Application objects based on various user-defined criteria.
    ApplicantFilterMenu
    ApplicantFilterMenu provides a user interface for filtering housing applications based on various applicant attributes such as age, marital status, and project details.
    ApplicantListMenu
    The ApplicantListMenu class provides a menu interface for managers to view a filtered list of applications.
    ApplicantMenu
    The ApplicantMenu class provides the main menu interface for applicants.
    ApplicantProjectMenu
    The ApplicantProjectMenu class provides a menu interface for applicants to interact with project-related options such as applying for a project or making enquiries.
    Application
    Represents an application for a housing project.
    Application.FlatType
    Enumeration of flat types available for application.
    Application.Status
    Enumeration of possible application statuses.
    Application.WithdrawStatus
    Enumeration of withdrawal statuses for an application.
    ApplicationListMenu
    The ApplicationListMenu class provides a menu interface for officers to view applications associated with a specific project.
    ApplicationManager
    This class manages the application process for the users (Applicants, Officers, and Managers).
    ApplicationMenu
    The ApplicationMenu class provides a menu interface for managing and viewing applications associated with a specific project.
    Applications
    The Applications class manages the list of applications in the system.
    ApplicationSelectMenu
    The ApplicationSelectMenu class provides a menu interface for officers to select an officer application by ID.
    ApplyMenu
    The ApplyMenu class provides a menu interface for applicants to apply for a project.
    ApplyMenu
    The ApplyMenu class provides a menu interface for officers to apply for a project.
    AppManager
    The AppManager class manages application startup procedures, including loading user and project data, and displaying the login menu.
    AppUserManager
    The AppUserManager class is responsible for managing the authentication and user-related actions.
    BookMenu
    The BookMenu class provides a menu interface for officers to book an application.
    CDFilterMenu
    CDFilterMenu provides a user interface for filtering housing applications based on the closing date of the housing project.
    CDFilterMenu
    The CDFilterMenu class provides a menu interface for filtering projects based on their closing dates.
    CreateMenu
    The CreateMenu class provides a menu interface for creating a new project.
    DeleteEnquiryMenu
    The EnquiryMenu class provides a menu interface for deleting enquiries
    DeleteMenu
    The DeleteMenu class provides a menu interface for deleting a project.
    EditApplicationMenu
    The EditApplicationMenu class provides a menu interface for modifying applications.
    EditEnquiryMenu
    The EnquiryMenu class provides a menu interface for editing enquiries
    EditMenu
    The EditMenu class provides a menu interface for editing project details.
    EditOApplicationMenu
    The EditOApplicationMenu class provides a menu interface for modifying officer applications.
    Enquiries
    This class manages a collection of enquiries and provides methods to filter them based on different roles (Applicant, Manager, Officer) and project.
    Enquiry
    Represents an enquiry made by an applicant regarding a project.
    EnquiryListMenu
    The EnquiryListMenu class provides a menu interface for listing enquiries.
    EnquiryManager
    EnquiryManager is responsible for managing enquiries related to projects.
    EnquiryMenu
    The EnquiryMenu class provides a menu interface for creating new enquiries related to a specific project.
    EnquirySelectMenu
    The EnquirySelectMenu class provides a menu interface for selecting a enquiry by ID.
    ExcelReader
     
    ExitMenu
    The ExitMenu class provides a menu option to exit the application.
    FlatTypeFilterMenu
    The FlatTypeFilterMenu class provides a menu for filtering applicants based on the type of flat they have applied for.
    FlatTypeFilterMenu
    The FlatTypeFilterMenu class provides a menu interface for filtering projects based on the availability of specific flat types (e.g., Two Room, Three Room).
    GetDate
    The GetDate class provides a utility method for prompting the user to input a date.
    HistoryMenu
    The HistoryMenu class provides a menu interface for applicants to view their application history.
    HistoryMenu
    The HistoryMenu class provides a menu interface for officers to view their application history.
    HomeMenu
    The HomeMenu class redirects users to their respective menus based on their user type.
    IdMenu
    The abstract IdMenu class provides a template for menus that require an ID to function, such as displaying a single project's details or performing operations on a specific item identified by an ID.
    Item
    Base class for all entities.
    ItemArray<T>
     
    LoginMenu
    The LoginMenu class provides a menu interface for users to log in to the application.
    LogoutMenu
    The LogoutMenu class provides a menu interface for users to log out of the application.
    LongStringifiable
    The LongStringifiable interface should be implemented by classes that can provide a more detailed, descriptive string representation of themselves.
    Manager
    The Manager class represents a user in the system who is a manager.
    ManagerMenu
    The ManagerMenu class provides the main menu interface for managers.
    ManagerProjectMenu
    The ManagerProjectMenu class provides a menu interface for managers to interact with project-related options such as editing, deleting, and managing applications.
    MaritalFilterMenu
    The MaritalFilterMenu class provides a menu for filtering applicants based on their marital status.
    Menu
    The abstract Menu class provides a template for different menu types in the system.
    NameFilterMenu
    The NameFilterMenu class provides a menu for filtering applicants based on their names.
    NameFilterMenu
    The NameFilterMenu class provides a menu interface for filtering projects based on their names.
    NeighFilterMenu
    The NeighFilterMenu class provides a menu interface for filtering applicants based on their neighbourhood.
    NeighFilterMenu
    The NeighFilterMenu class provides a menu interface for filtering projects based on their neighbourhoods.
    ODFilterMenu
    The ODFilterMenu class provides a menu interface for filtering applicants based on project opening dates.
    ODFilterMenu
    The ODFilterMenu class provides a menu interface for filtering projects based on their opening dates.
    Officer
    The Officer class represents a user in the system who is an officer.
    OfficerApplication
    Represents an officer's application to a project.
    OfficerApplicationManager
    This class handles the management of Officer Applications, including the ability to apply for an officer position, approve or withdraw an application, and approve or reject a withdrawal request.
    OfficerApplicationMenu
    The OfficerApplicationMenu class provides a menu interface for managing and viewing officer applications associated with a specific project.
    OfficerApplications
    OfficerApplications is a utility class that handles operations related to officer applications.
    OfficerMenu
    The OfficerMenu class provides the main menu interface for officers.
    OfficerProjectMenu
    The OfficerProjectMenu class provides a menu interface for officers to interact with project-related options such as managing applications, viewing receipts, and replying to enquiries.
    PasswordChangeMenu
    The PasswordChangeMenu class provides a menu interface for users to change their password.
    Project
    Represents a housing project with different types of flats, managed by a manager.
    ProjectDetails
    The ProjectDetails class provides an abstract menu for handling project details.
    ProjectFilterManager
    ProjectFilterManager provides static filtering functionality for a list of housing projects based on various criteria such as flat type availability, project name, neighborhood, and dates.
    ProjectFilterMenu
    The ProjectFilterMenu class provides a menu interface for applying filters to projects.
    ProjectInchargeMenu
    The ProjectInchargeMenu class provides a menu interface for managers to view the list of projects they are in charge of.
    ProjectListMenu
    The ProjectListMenu class provides a menu interface for listing projects.
    ProjectManager
    ProjectManager is responsible for managing the lifecycle of a project.
    Projects
    The `Projects` class manages the list of projects in the system.
    ProjectSelectMenu
    The ProjectSelectMenu class provides a menu interface for selecting a project by ID.
    ProjectViewMenu
    The ProjectViewMenu class provides a menu interface for viewing detailed information about a specific project.
    ReceiptMenu
    The ReceiptMenu class provides a menu interface for officers to view detailed receipts of applications associated with a specific project.
    ReplyEnquiryMenu
    The ReplyEnquiryMenu class provides a menu interface for replying to enquiries related to a specific project.
    StatusMenu
    The StatusMenu class provides a menu interface for applicants to check the status of their current application.
    Stringifiable
    The Stringifiable interface is intended for classes that want to provide a standardized string representation of their instances.
    Test
    The Test class contains a series of test cases to validate the functionality of the HDB Management System.
    ToggleVisibilityMenu
    The ToggleVisibilityMenu class provides a menu interface for toggling the visibility of a project.
    User
    The User class represents a user in the system.
    User.MaritalStatus
    Enum representing the marital status of a user.
    User.UserType
    Enum representing the different types of users.
    Users
    The `Users` class manages the collection of all users in the system.
    Validator
    The Validator class provides utility methods for validating various user inputs and project details.
    ViewMenu
    The ViewMenu class provides a menu interface for officers to view the project associated with a selected officer application.
    WithdrawMenu
    The WithdrawMenu class provides a menu interface for applicants to request the withdrawal of their application.
    WithdrawMenu
    The WithdrawMenu class provides a menu interface for officers to request the withdrawal of their officer application.
